HEADWORD: Weely
<hw>Weel"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw><ety>[Prov. E. <ets>weel</ets>, <ets>weal</ets>, a wicker basket
to catch eels; prob. akin to <ets>willow</ets>, and so called as made of
willow twigs.]</ety> <def>A kind of trap or snare for fish, made of
twigs.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Carew.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

